1
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:14,760
<i>Chan, you should</i>
<i>tell the chairman the truth</i>

2
00:00:14,840 --> 00:00:17,720
<i>about why his beloved granddaughter</i>
<i>can't attend the event.</i>

3
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:18,960
- You bitch.
- Let go!

4
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:19,800
Cha!

5
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:21,440
How could something like this happen?

6
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,520
<i>What happened to him?</i>

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,240
Mr. Thiwa had
an acute myocardial infarction.

8
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:28,840
<i>I know Alzheimer's medication</i>
<i>is expensive.</i>

9
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:31,480
<i>If you want to repay me,</i>
<i>I have a job for you.</i>

10
00:00:31,560 --> 00:00:32,840
Socialite Claire.

11
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,200
Hello.

12
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:50,200
Hello.

13
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,280
Ms. Claire? Ms. Claire!

14
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:01,960
Ms. Claire, what are you doing?!

15
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,600
Who are you?

16
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:13,520
I'm Jinla. From <i>The Contenic.</i>

17
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:15,760
You scheduled an interview with me.

18
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:20,360
Okay. You're here.

19
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,760
Do I need to introduce myself?

20
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,560
I don't think so.

21
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,680
You must have done your homework.

22
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,320
- Right?
- Yes.

23
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,480
You are Ms. Khaedarun Kanchathara,

24
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,680
Vice President of TGL Group,

25
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:37,040
a real estate company

26
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,280
- ranked third in--
- Enough.

27
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,600
Shall we go?

28
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:43,800
Go where?

29
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,960
I'd rather walk and talk.

30
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:49,440
- Uh…
- That way, you'll learn

31
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:52,240
and see more than
the information you already have.

32
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,200
Oh, sure.

33
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,160
What did your company brief you on?

34
00:01:56,720 --> 00:02:00,040
Uh, just to come
and interview you, Ms. Claire.

35
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:03,120
Anything you want to
ask me before we start?

36
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,560
You can ask me anything.

37
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,680
You can ask about yesterday.

38
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:10,400
Why were you standing
on the edge of the balcony?

39
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,760
I was looking for a way to die.

40
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:46,080
Have you ever thought about
how you would die?

41
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,560
No.

42
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:51,120
Do you know why I asked you
to interview me?

43
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:58,440
Is it because you want to create content
so people can get to know you better?

44
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,280
I want a book to hand out at the funeral.

45
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,360
Funeral?

46
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,240
Whose funeral?

47
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,760
You're interviewing me, so obviously mine.

48
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:14,840
I plan to die when I'm 45.

49
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,519
Certainly no later than 50.

50
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,680
Why's that, Ms. Claire?

51
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,519
Are you sick or something?

52
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,280
No.

53
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,360
Because by then,
my grandpa won't be around.

54
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:28,520
And besides,

55
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,320
look at me now.

56
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,080
I already have everything.

57
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:35,200
What else is there to live for?

58
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:38,880
To enjoy what you have.

59
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,440
If you were an actress,

60
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,920
would you want to be remembered
as the number one leading lady

61
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:55,000
or as someone so old no one hires you
unless it's to play a mother?

62
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,880
That's how I am.

63
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:01,080
I want people to remember me

64
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,320
as Khaedarun,

65
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,840
the woman who has everything.

66
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:12,320
Come on. Let's talk by the pool.

67
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,440
Oh, they're still here?

68
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:30,560
That's Ms. Patchy and Ms. Yo.

69
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,040
They're famous.

70
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,240
Hey.

71
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:37,760
- Hey.
- Hey.

72
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,280
- Claire!
- Claire!

73
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,520
- My turn.
- Come here.

74
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,200
Hello.

75
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,160
Hey, want to keep going?

76
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,040
I can't. I have to work.

77
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,720
Don't you have a drama to shoot?

78
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:54,360
I do, but I'd rather
hang out with my friend.

79
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,280
Who's that?

80
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,320
She's interviewing me. Her name is Jinla.

81
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,240
- Hi, Jin.
- Hi, Jin.

82
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,520
Hi.

83
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,680
What's wrong?
Why are you making that face?

84
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:09,000
Uh, I'm a fan of Ms. Patchy.

85
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,920
I didn't know she was your friend.

86
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,200
This is how they are.

87
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:17,320
They hang out here whenever they're free.
They barely go home.

88
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,840
You want anything? I'll go get it for you.

89
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,400
No, it's okay. Have fun.

90
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,520
- See you.
- Bye-bye.

91
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:31,640
Do you want to swim?

92
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,920
No.

93
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,920
I can't swim.

94
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,600
Really?

95
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,200
Then we have that in common.

96
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,400
Isn't it strange?

97
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:43,080
I have a pool at home, but I can't swim.

98
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,960
Do you know why I haven't
taken swimming lessons?

99
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,040
I don't know.

100
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:05,520
Because I think…

101
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,480
maybe…

102
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,080
I want to drown myself someday.

103
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:19,840
Uh, Ms. Claire, then maybe you should

104
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,520
step away from the edge.

105
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,640
I occurred to me

106
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:27,720
that drowning must be
the most painful way to die.

107
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:34,320
If I'm going to die,
I should pick the most painful way, right?

108
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,120
Please don't, Ms. Claire.

109
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,680
Ms. Claire!

110
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:48,840
Help!

111
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,080
Help! Ms. Claire fell into the pool!

112
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,120
Help!

113
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,560
- Help!
- Ms. Claire!

114
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,640
Help!

115
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,760
Help! Ms. Claire fell into the pool!

116
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,680
- Help!
- Help!

117
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,880
Ms. Claire! Ms. Claire!

118
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,000
Ms. Claire!

119
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,040
Ms. Claire! Help!

120
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,480
Ms. Claire!

121
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,280
How was that?

122
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,360
What were you doing?

123
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,720
Were you trying to kill me?

124
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,360
I just wanted you to know
what it's like to almost die.

125
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:20,800
If you don't know,
how can you write about it properly?

126
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,320
Are you out of your mind?

127
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:31,120
Just follow me. I'll get you changed.

128
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:40,640
<i>Wan, you knew it would</i>
<i>turn out like this, didn't you?</i>

129
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,480
<i>That's why you sent me instead.</i>

130
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,120
This way, ma'am.

131
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:20,120
I chose this for you.
This outfit should suit you.

132
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:25,680
It's okay. Once my clothes dry,
I'll wear my own.

133
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,040
I said change.

134
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,600
You'll get sick wearing wet clothes.

135
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:38,000
Please change. See me outside after.

136
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:54,560
It fits perfectly. You look beautiful.

137
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:58,040
We'll take care of your clothes for you.

138
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,840
Thank you.

139
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,440
Claire?

140
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,920
Who are you?

141
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,000
Sorry.

142
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,080
I'm sorry.

143
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,920
Oh, you've met?

144
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,720
Perfect.
You look beautiful in this outfit.

145
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,240
I'm glad you two met,

146
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,280
have you guys talked?

147
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,320
Not yet.

148
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,320
This is Chan.

149
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,560
He's my fiancé.

150
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:36,280
- Your fiancé?
- Yes.

151
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,640
We agreed this would be
an in-depth interview.

152
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:42,000
So I want you to know everything about me.

153
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:48,280
Chan, this is Jinla,
the interviewer I told you about.

154
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:51,400
Hello.

155
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,680
Hello.

156
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:57,960
Sorry I'm late. I stopped by the hospital.

157
00:12:58,040 --> 00:12:59,720
Did Grandpa want something?

158
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,600
No, I was just making sure he was okay.

159
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,160
Well, that's good.

160
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,520
Shall we continue our talk in the car?

161
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,160
I asked Chan to drive us.

162
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,760
Where are we going?

163
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:20,840
We're taking a helicopter
to see the project I'm overseeing.

164
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:21,760
Shall we?

165
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,360
Come on. Let's go.

166
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:32,240
I can do this.
I can do this. I can do this.

167
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:07,120
Have you ever been on a helicopter?

168
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,080
This is my first time.

169
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:17,080
Oh, if you want to
ask him anything, feel free.

170
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:21,840
I'm just a little surprised.

171
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:24,960
Because I had no information
that you were in a relationship.

172
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,920
Then suddenly,
I found out you were engaged.

173
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,480
So I didn't prepare any questions.

174
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:33,040
Chan is quiet.
He doesn't really socialize.

175
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:34,640
In that case,

176
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:40,240
why don't you briefly
introduce yourself, darling?

177
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,280
It's alright.

178
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,200
She's here for you.

179
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,480
She doesn't need to know about me.

180
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:02,000
There you have it.

181
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:14,360
It's time. Let's go.

182
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,160
I've spoken to the captain.

183
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,040
The weather is clear today.

184
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,240
He'll fly you around the project site.

185
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,600
If you need anything else,
just let him know.

186
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:31,360
Are you really not coming with us?

187
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:33,640
I have work to do.

188
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:38,000
I hope you didn't tell the pilot
to crash the helicopter.

189
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:43,000
You're not even going to laugh?

190
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,360
Okay, then kiss me goodbye.

191
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:56,000
Let me know when you get back.

192
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,120
I'll have someone pick you up.

193
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,480
Don't mind him.

194
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,200
That's just how he is. Let's go.

195
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,560
Are we almost there, Captain?

196
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,320
Yes, Ms. Claire.

197
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:58,160
We're now entering Nakhon Nayok.

198
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:00,040
We'll arrive in five minutes.

199
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,920
The weather is good today.

200
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,680
Please enjoy viewing the project.

201
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,240
Here.

202
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,480
The project we're seeing today.

203
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,079
It's called Agriv.

204
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:19,520
Agriv?

205
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,040
Short for Agriculture Village.

206
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:25,160
A residential project
focused on agriculture.

207
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,359
To put it simply,

208
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:30,720
we created this project for people
who love nature and farming

209
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,640
but don't want to give up technology.

210
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:36,080
What is it?

211
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:39,680
Nothing.

212
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:45,520
I just didn't think you would be
interested in this kind of thing.

213
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:48,680
When it's business,

214
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:52,640
even if we hate something,
we have to do it.

215
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:57,680
Was that clever, Ms. Jin?

216
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:00,200
I like it. It sounds good.

217
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,080
Make sure to put it in the book.

218
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,160
Oh, yes.

219
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,560
Ms. Claire?

220
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,200
You said

221
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:31,400
you'd have nothing to live for
once your grandfather was gone.

222
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:34,880
But what about Mr. Chan, your fiancé?

223
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:35,800
What about him?

224
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,320
Well…

225
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,320
people who are engaged
are supposed to love each other.

226
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,600
Aren't you worried…

227
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:47,040
he would be sad
if something happened to you?

228
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:51,040
Sad?

229
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:57,640
I think he'd be
the happiest one if I died.

230
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,360
Do you know

231
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:06,800
why I keep looking for ways to die?

232
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,640
Because if I don't die by my own hand,

233
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:16,880
I'll die at the hands of someone
in that house anyway.

234
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,720
You have no idea

235
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:22,560
how dangerous is it to live in that house.

236
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,280
Something wrong, Captain?

237
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:44,840
No, ma'am.

238
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:57,600
Claire, you bitch. Where are you?

239
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,560
Huh? Where are you?!

240
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,560
You want what's mine so badly, huh?

241
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,680
What are you looking at?

242
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,600
- I'll handle this.
- Where are you?

243
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:07,440
Huh? You want what's mine so badly?

244
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:08,640
- Ms. Cha.
- Bitch!

245
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:10,040
That's enough, Ms. Cha!

246
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:14,040
If the chairman finds out about this,
he'll be upset.

247
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:20,360
How dare you use my dad to threaten me?

248
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:25,600
I really wanna know
if Claire feeds you dry food or wet food.

249
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,400
Why are you so loyal to her?

250
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:30,280
Feel better after slapping me?

251
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:32,800
If you do, please leave Ms. Claire's room.

252
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,080
No! I'm not leaving!

253
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,720
I won't leave until I know where she is.

254
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,360
I don't know. She didn't tell me anything.

255
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,640
You don't know?

256
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,640
Claire!

257
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,280
Claire!

258
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:48,920
- Where are you?! What are you looking at?!
- Ms. Cha.

259
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,000
- Where is Claire?
- Ms. Cha.

260
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:54,360
Claire, I know you're home!
Come out right now!

261
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:55,280
- Ms. Cha.
- Claire!

262
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:57,360
Please stop. She really isn't here.

263
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,720
Don't lie to me.

264
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:00,800
Where else could she be?

265
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:02,080
Claire!

266
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,560
Come out right now!

267
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:04,840
Claire!

268
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:07,440
Claire, I said come out!

269
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,760
Claire!

270
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:11,040
Are you done?

271
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:15,520
What would you do
if you knew where Claire was?

272
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:18,640
Didn't yesterday's livestream
get enough attention already?

273
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:19,880
No, it didn't.

274
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:23,280
Because if it did,
you'd know what she did to me.

275
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,640
Oh, I forgot.

276
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:29,160
A former maid who somehow
became the chairman's wife

277
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,440
wouldn't dare stand up to
his real granddaughter, right?

278
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:38,920
Good for you.

279
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:43,200
But actually you should've
slapped me in front of Dad.

280
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,480
You would've scored more points with him.

281
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:49,760
Cha! Cha!

282
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,040
So where's Ms. Claire?

283
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,360
Hello?

284
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,640
What?

285
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:23,920
Is something wrong?

286
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:28,480
No. Please excuse me.

287
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,120
What's up, Tun?

288
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,080
Chan.

289
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:55,040
You haven't heard
about Ms. Claire, have you?

290
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,480
What did she do this time?

291
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,080
Chan.

292
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:02,000
Brace yourself.

293
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:05,640
<i>The Nakhon Nayok police</i>
<i>called me. They said…</i>

294
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,760
her helicopter crashed.

295
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:12,960
And…

296
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,640
how is she?

297
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:19,520
From what I know so far,
there's only one survivor.

298
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,800
Did they say who?

299
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:32,080
You still don't know why I slapped you?

300
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,480
I do.

301
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:37,200
You slapped me because I slapped Claire,

302
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,200
the princess of the Kanchathara family.

303
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:43,960
I'm sorry I called her Claire.

304
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,840
From now on, I'll call her Ms. Claire

305
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,480
so you won't be angry with me again.

306
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:49,560
Listen.

307
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:54,360
I slapped you because
you almost let Claire get everything.

308
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:55,920
You know that right now

309
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,360
your father's will leave
everything to Claire.

310
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:02,520
If anything happens to him now,
everything will go to her.

311
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,400
Is that why

312
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:10,960
you're letting Claire run this house
even though you're Dad's wife?

313
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:12,000
Yes.

314
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:15,280
I'll put up with it
until we get everything.

315
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:19,160
And when that day comes,
do whatever you want to her,

316
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,240
and I'll join you.

317
00:26:30,960 --> 00:26:33,600
What is it? I told you
I'm not going to the office.

318
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:38,000
What?

319
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:45,320
What is it?

320
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:48,840
Mom.

321
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:54,560
The helicopter Claire took to see
the Nakhon Nayok project crashed.

322
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,000
Looks like

323
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:06,040
we don't have to wait for your father
to change his will in our favor anymore.

324
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,320
Let's go.

325
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,520
Where are we going?

326
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,640
To tell your father

327
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:16,240
that his beloved granddaughter Claire's
helicopter crashed.

328
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:18,920
Aren't you worried
he'll have a heart attack?

329
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:23,960
You said he had to change his will
in our favor first before he could die.

330
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:28,040
If Claire was still alive,
everything would go to her.

331
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:30,160
But now that Claire is gone,

332
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,920
that means…

333
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,000
it would only go to you and me.

334
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:43,480
<i>Did they say who?</i>

335
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:45,280
They didn't say anything.

336
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:47,280
<i>So are you going to Nakhon Nayok now?</i>

337
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,200
<i>I'll coordinate everything.</i>

338
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:50,400
You go ahead.

339
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:53,800
And keep this quiet.
Don't let the press find out.

340
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,560
<i>What about you?</i>

341
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:57,320
<i>I'm informing the chairman first.</i>

342
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:59,200
<i>He has a heart condition.</i>

343
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,920
<i>I'm worried</i>

344
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,160
<i>if he finds out about</i>

345
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:06,160
<i>Ms. Claire's helicopter crash,</i>
<i>he won't be able to take it.</i>

346
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,760
Why are you all here?

347
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,240
Don't you have work to do?

348
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,160
Honey…

349
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:57,160
Why are you just standing there?
Say what you have to say.

350
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:00,960
If you're here to apologize
about Claire yesterday,

351
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:04,200
I think you should apologize
to Claire instead.

352
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:13,760
Dad, I actually wanted to apologize
to Claire myself.

353
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,760
If…

354
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:22,160
If what? Just say it.

355
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:23,920
Well…

356
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,040
we…

357
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:29,320
wanted to tell you about Claire.

358
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:34,640
What about her?

359
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,360
Tun.

360
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:43,480
Who survived?

361
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,400
Dad.

362
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:53,680
Dad.

363
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:05,400
Chan.

364
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:10,560
Did Claire's helicopter really crash?

365
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:19,720
Just tell him if it's true or not.

366
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:26,200
It's true.

367
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:30,920
Dad.

368
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,960
Cha, go get a doctor. Hurry.

369
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:35,560
- Yes.
- But I received a report that

370
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:38,160
Claire is the only survivor, sir.

371
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:44,320
A helicopter crash and she didn't die?

372
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,600
Who would believe that?

373
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,560
Chan.

374
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:50,680
I know you're worried about him,

375
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:54,080
afraid he won't be able to take it
if something happened to Claire.

376
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:56,080
But it's better to be honest now

377
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:58,120
than letting him find out later.

378
00:30:58,200 --> 00:30:59,400
I'm not finished.

379
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:03,160
Claire did survive,

380
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:05,360
but she's in a critical condition.

381
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:08,960
Go get a nurse to unhook me from all this.

382
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,840
- Dad, where are you going?
- Lie back down.

383
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:14,440
Claire's badly hurt.
You expect me to just lie here?

384
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:16,600
Arrange everything. I'm going to see her.

385
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,120
Don't go, sir.

386
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:21,680
If you go, this will become major news.

387
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:24,880
And it will affect our company's stock.

388
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:28,440
I've told Tun to coordinate
and keep this as quiet as possible.

389
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,120
But we're her family.

390
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:36,240
At least, we need to know
if she's dead or alive.

391
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:38,960
Or you don't want my dad to go

392
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:41,720
because you don't want him
to know she's actually dead?

393
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:44,880
It seems you really want
Claire dead, Ms. Cha.

394
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:47,960
You should say
she wants to know the truth.

395
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:50,080
Enough, enough, enough!

396
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:51,960
Chan.

397
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:54,800
Yes?

398
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:57,600
Claire really isn't dead?

399
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:00,920
She's not.

400
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:08,600
Then do everything you can to save her.

401
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:11,600
Find the best doctors.

402
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:14,080
I don't care how much it costs.

403
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:17,400
Do whatever it takes to save her.

404
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,320
I will.

405
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:25,240
Chan.

406
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,320
Promise me.

407
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:32,200
Promise you'll save Claire.

408
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:42,480
I promise.

409
00:32:58,120 --> 00:33:01,480
ACCIDENT AND EMERGENCY WARD

410
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:02,680
How is Ms. Claire?

411
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,080
- It's quite worrying.
- Tun!

412
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:05,760
Chan.

413
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:09,200
He's been treating Ms. Claire
since she was brought here.

414
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:10,240
How is she, Doctor?

415
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,880
Her condition is quite worrying.

416
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:14,640
Burns cover almost 80% of her body.

417
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:17,679
Tun.

418
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:21,960
Tell the press Claire is the survivor.

419
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,800
As for the details of her treatment,

420
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,080
we'll keep them confidential.

421
00:34:31,639 --> 00:34:32,560
Okay.

422
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:39,800
Tell me.
How serious is Claire's condition?

423
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:44,800
The doctor said her internal organs
are severely damaged.

424
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:48,360
<i>And burns cover about 80% of her body.</i>

425
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:52,040
Especially on…

426
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,600
her face.

427
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:56,920
Enough. That's enough.

428
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:00,560
<i>Chan.</i>

429
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,840
Please save her.

430
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:07,920
I will.

431
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:56,160
TWO MONTHS LATER

432
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:58,800
<i>All her vital signs are normal now.</i>

433
00:35:58,880 --> 00:36:02,880
Her heart, lungs,
and blood pressure are all fine.

434
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:06,320
And her surgical wounds
show no sign of infection.

435
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:08,960
<i>Where am I?</i>

436
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:12,720
<i>Am I dead?</i>

437
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:15,840
<i>Who is that?</i>

438
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,080
<i>A doctor?</i>

439
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:21,440
When will she need another surgery?

440
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:24,360
We have to wait until she's more stable.

441
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:26,040
<i>Surgery?</i>

442
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:28,000
- Thank you.
<i>- What surgery?</i>

443
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:29,320
<i>Whose surgery?</i>

444
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:31,360
<i>Do they mean me?</i>

445
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:41,360
Can you hear me?

446
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:44,480
<i>Whose voice is that?</i>

447
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:47,760
It's me, Chan.

448
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:51,320
Can you hear me, Claire?

449
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:53,960
<i>Chan?</i>

450
00:36:55,560 --> 00:36:58,120
This is Chan, my fiancé.

451
00:36:58,920 --> 00:36:59,840
Hello.

452
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:03,880
<i>Mr. Chan, Ms. Claire's fiancé.</i>

453
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,320
<i>Then…</i>

454
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,960
<i>why is he in my room?</i>

455
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:12,160
I don't know if you can hear me.

456
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,440
But I believe you can feel this.

457
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,600
<i>Yes, I can.</i>

458
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:22,600
<i>But… but why are you holding my hand?</i>

459
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:24,000
<i>I'm not Ms. Claire.</i>

460
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:28,960
What's happening, Doctor?

461
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:32,080
Ms. Claire has been in a coma
for almost two months.

462
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:35,160
Now that all her organs
are starting to function,

463
00:37:35,240 --> 00:37:39,000
she may be startled
and her body hasn't adjusted yet.

464
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:42,000
Don't be scared, Ms. Claire.

465
00:37:42,080 --> 00:37:46,520
When you wake up again,
your body will be more functional.

466
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:56,720
We need to put you back to sleep.

467
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,760
<i>No. No, no, no, wait.</i>

468
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:01,280
<i>I want to know what happened to me.</i>

469
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:09,920
<i>Wait, I want to know what happened to me.</i>

470
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:13,120
<i>Wait. Why am I not dead? What happened?</i>

471
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:36,040
FOUR MONTHS LATER, PRESENT DAY

472
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:50,400
I'm going to remove the eye bandages now.

473
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:03,080
Open your eyes slowly.

474
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,560
Can you see me?

475
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:34,160
Claire?

476
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:41,840
You had a breathing tube in
for a long time.

477
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:43,680
It must still hurt.

478
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:46,920
Doctor, please.

479
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:55,440
I'm going to remove
the bandages on your face now.

480
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:57,120
Are you ready?

481
00:39:58,520 --> 00:39:59,880
<i>So ready.</i>

482
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:04,200
<i>They'll finally know</i>
<i>that I'm Jinla, not Ms. Claire.</i>

483
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:07,320
<i>It must have been a mistake.</i>

484
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,760
<i>Yes, it must have been then.</i>

485
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:21,120
<i>They mixed up my name with Ms. Claire's.</i>

486
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:24,440
<i>That's why everyone thinks I'm her.</i>

487
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:30,840
Are you ready to look in the mirror?

488
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:55,320
<i>No.</i>

489
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:57,000
<i>No.</i>

490
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,560
<i>Why do I look like…</i>

491
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:03,040
<i>Ms. Claire?</i>

492
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,480
<i>This can't be real.</i>

493
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,720
<i>I can feel it.</i>

494
00:41:09,360 --> 00:41:11,040
This is my cheek.

495
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:12,640
<i>Are these really my eyes?</i>

496
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:17,080
Claire?

497
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:20,440
Do you remember
what happened on the helicopter?

498
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:39,840
Claire. Claire, don't be scared.
You're safe now.

499
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:42,120
Everyone's okay now.

500
00:41:43,560 --> 00:41:44,400
<i>Claire?</i>

501
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:47,920
<i>Am I really Ms. Claire?</i>

502
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:56,600
But… what about Jinla?

503
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:02,880
She…

504
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:11,560
She died at the scene.

505
00:42:18,320 --> 00:42:20,640
<i>I'm… I'm dead?</i>

506
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:23,760
<i>But… I'm still here.</i>

507
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,440
<i>Then why am I Ms. Claire?</i>

508
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:38,120
<i>What happened to me?</i>

509
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:40,920
I'm… I'm not dead.

510
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:42,440
Yes, Claire, you're not dead.

511
00:42:42,520 --> 00:42:43,680
- Prepare a sedative.
- Claire.

512
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,920
But you can't walk yet.
You've been sleeping.

513
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,160
Your muscles are weak.

514
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:48,640
- You need physical therapy.
- No.

515
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:49,920
I'm not Ms. Claire.

516
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,840
- I'm not Ms. Claire.
- You are Ms. Khaedarun.

517
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:52,840
- Let go.
- Claire.

518
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:53,960
- Let go!
- Claire.

519
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,680
I'm going to give her a sedative.

520
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:58,280
Wait. Claire, listen to me.

521
00:42:58,360 --> 00:42:59,880
Claire, listen to me!

522
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:05,360
What we're about to do
is give you that sedative.

523
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:10,720
And it will put you back to sleep.

524
00:43:11,720 --> 00:43:13,400
But you just woke up.

525
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:16,640
You don't wanna go back to sleep, do you?

526
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:25,320
Then you need to stay still.

527
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:31,520
Claire.

528
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:34,120
I'll leave you alone.

529
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:39,280
But you have to promise me

530
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:42,320
you won't act like this again.

531
00:43:44,040 --> 00:43:45,640
I know you just woke up.

532
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:49,600
You're still confused
and can't think straight, right?

533
00:43:51,720 --> 00:43:54,040
But I need you to remember one thing.

534
00:43:56,800 --> 00:43:58,520
You are Ms. Khaedarun.

535
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:39,160
Do you really think
she's ready to see the chairman?

536
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:40,480
She has to be.

537
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:44,760
But if we take her back,

538
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,200
won't that make things even worse?

539
00:44:50,640 --> 00:44:54,280
If she doesn't go back now,
she may never be able to.

540
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:56,440
Don't forget.

541
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:59,000
We brought her here because
the people there don't want her back.

542
00:45:00,120 --> 00:45:01,000
Besides,

543
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:03,720
she can't stay here forever.

544
00:45:04,240 --> 00:45:07,720
Because the person who can
keep her safest is her grandfather.

545
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:11,040
What we have to do now is…

546
00:45:11,120 --> 00:45:14,240
make Claire return to her old self
as much as possible.

547
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:02,640
<i>That was just a nightmare.</i>

548
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:05,800
<i>I'm not Ms. Claire.</i>

549
00:46:06,800 --> 00:46:08,200
<i>I'm not Ms. Claire.</i>

550
00:46:37,360 --> 00:46:39,200
<i>Am I Ms. Claire?</i>

551
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:41,520
<i>Am I Ms. Claire?</i>

552
00:47:33,320 --> 00:47:35,240
I'm Jinla.

553
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:38,400
<i>If you won't behave</i>
<i>and keep making a scene,</i>

554
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:41,160
you'll be given a sedative.

555
00:47:41,240 --> 00:47:42,280
Is Claire really awake?

556
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:45,320
<i>Then why haven't you brought her back?</i>

557
00:47:45,400 --> 00:47:49,280
I will definitely bring her back
to her own home.

558
00:47:50,680 --> 00:47:54,080
<i>Tun, we need to find her</i>
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

559
00:47:54,160 --> 00:47:56,360
<i>If she tells anyone</i>
<i>we turned her into Claire,</i>

560
00:47:56,440 --> 00:47:58,960
<i>everything we've planned will be in vain.</i>
